                                            <h5>
                                                <b>APPEALS:</b>
                                            </h5>
                                            <ol>
                                                <p>
                                                    1. e.g. student may appeal through the Head of Department and the
                                                    Dean of the Faculty for a reassessment of the Examination script on
                                                    payment of a fee of N400.00 per course unit. If the appeal results
                                                    in a significant improvement (i.e, a change in later grade) on the
                                                    student original grade the Appeal fee shall be refunded to the
                                                    appellant.
                                                </p>
                                            </ol>
                                            <ol>
                                                <p>
                                                    No person can appeal for the reassessment of the scripts of some
                                                    other student. </p>
                                            </ol>
                                            <ol>
                                                <p>
                                                    For group appeal to be valid, notice in writing of such an appeal
                                                    must be lodged with the registrar within four weeks after Senate
                                                    approval of the particular results.
                                                </p>
                                            </ol>
                                        </ul>
