                                        <ul>
                                            <h5>
                                                <b>REPEATING FAILED COURSES:</b>
                                            </h5>
                                            <ol>
                                                <p>
                                                    A student shall repeat a course or courses failed at the next
                                                    available opportunity provided the total number of credit hours
                                                    during that semester is not more than 24. A student repeating a
                                                    course shall retain the grade earned in that course. The grade point
                                                    earned at first and subsequent attempts shall count towards the
                                                    student’s Cumulative Grade Point Average (CGPA).
                                                </p>
                                            </ol>
                                        </ul>
                                    </div>
                                </div>

                                <div class="row">
                                    <div class="col-md-12 mb-12">
                                        <ul>
                                            <h5>
                                                <b>PROBATION:</b>
                                            </h5>
                                            <ol>
                                                <p>
                                                    Probation is a status granted to a student - <br>
                                                    <b>1.</b> Who fails up to 10 Credit Units and CGPA is less than
                                                    1.50. <br>
                                                    <b>2.</b> Who fails up to 15 Credit Units and CGPA is less than
                                                    1.50.
                                                    Such student shall be required to repeat only the courses of the
                                                    previous year and will not take on any new course. The student will
                                                    be credited with grade earned during the first attempt and during
                                                    the second probation year. At the end of the probation year, the
                                                    student’s CGPA will be calculated based on the two sets of results.
                                                </p>
                                            </ol>
                                        </ul>
                                    </div>
                                </div>

                                <div class="row">
                                    <div class="col-md-12 mb-12">
                                        <ul>
                                            <h5>
                                                <b>WITHDRAWAL:</b>
                                            </h5>
                                            <ol>
                                                <p>
                                                    1. A student who fails up to 15 credit Units but CGPA is less than
                                                    1.5 should withdraw from the University or change course. <br>
                                                    2. A student who fails more than 15 Credit Units should withdraw.
                                                </p>
                                            </ol>
                                        </ul>
                                    </div>
                                </div>

